1. Create mariadb pod use -e to pass env variable to the pod 
2. Create a svc without exposing
3. connect to the service with another pod
Note: search about mysql client 
4. connect to the client pod using k exec -it <podname> -- /bin/bash
5. if you are stuck in (3,4), just create port-forward and connect to the database
Notes
1. k run --help   => use to know how to run a pod
2. k describe  <podname> => to get pod lables and any info about it 
